Five tribes, totaling 989 individuals, survived the recent onslaught.
Among them are the Onge, Sentinelese, Andamanese, Jarawa, and Shompen tribes.
The Onge tribe faces territorial threats due to government development projects.
The Indian navy searched for aborigines on the Nicobar islands to prevent their extinction.
The tsunami caused significant damage to marine life and coastal areas.
Mangroves and coral reefs play a crucial role in protecting against such disasters.
Conservation efforts are essential to preserve these ecosystems and prevent future devastation.
The Indonesian government is taking steps to assess and mitigate the impact of the tsunami in Aceh.
